really great... As others have suggested, don't follow the instructions to layer the ganaches, but pour them on one at a time when they're still warm, letting each layer cool thoroughly. This will make them smooth and even and the chocolate ganache will even be a bit shiny. Then freeze the whole thing after removing from the pan and before cutting into squares to make sure the layers don't smear together. This step ensures good color distinction. If you don't happen to have crème de menthe on hand, that's alright. A little extra mint extract will do. A simpler flavor, but still rich.

