I made these as the gifts that I gave out to my co-workers. They were a huge hit! I didn't cool the top two layers before pouring them which made it much easier to pour and spread. Keeping the knife clean during cutting is vital, or it can get messy! These are wonderfully delicious!

Rating: 4
Amazingly rich, impressive presentation. As others have mentioned, there is no need to do the cooling/spreading described in the recipe -- I just completely cooled the brownie, then made the white chocolate layer and poured that on top. Allow that to COMPLETELY cool, then make the dark chocolate top layer and pour on top. Wipe the knife clean between cuts, and re-cool if it starts getting messy. Really, quite an easy recipe for such an impressive looking/tasting dessert, the hardest part was the cutting! I also used pepermint schnapps, as I couldn't find creme de menthe, and although the middle layer is white instead of green, it tastes divine.

